le%20it%20raised%20a%20retractable%2C%20'optoelectronic%20mast'%20to%20fire%20at%20satellites%2C%20before%20diving%20back%20down%20to%20depth%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Hong%20Kong's%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fchina%2Fscience%2Farticle%2F3270890%2Fchina-could-attack-starlink-satellites-%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESouth%20China%20Morning%20Post%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20citing%20the%20study%2C%20which%20was%20published%20in%20the%20Chinese%20defense%20magazine%20%26quot%3BCommand%20Control%20%26amp%3B%20Simulation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Chinese%20researchers%20contrasted%20this%20approach%20with%20current%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-could-blind-us-with-nuclear-space-weapon-ex-cia-director-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eanti-satellite%20weapons%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20use%20ground-fired%20rockets%20to%20launch%20what%20is%20essentially%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.armscontrol.org%2Fact%2F2022-03%2Ffeatures%2Frussias-anti-satellite-weapons-asymmetric-response-us-aerospace-superiority%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ekiller%20satellite%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20destroys%20its%20prey%20with%20an%20explosive%20warhead%20or%20projectile.%20The%20US%20government%20recently%20warned%20that%20Russia%20is%20also%20developing%20an%20anti-satellite%20with%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F16%2Fpolitics%2Frussia-nuclear-space-weapon-intelligence%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enuclear%20warhead%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20A%20laser%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20offers%20the%20potential%20to%20fire%20at%20many%20space%20targets%20but%20also%20comes%20with%20the%20many%20complexities%20of%20submarine%20operations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20technologies%2C%20which%20began%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20were%20conceived%20for%20an%20era%20when%20satellites%20were%20big%2C%20expensive%20and%20few%20in%20number.%20They%20remain%20a%20threat%20to%20sophisticated%20spy%20and%20communications%20satellites%2C%20but%20the%20advent%20of%20cheap%2C%20expendable%20swarms%20of%20communications%20satellites%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Starlink%20commercial%20network%2C%20has%20vastly%20complicated%20anti-satellite%20efforts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BTaking%20the%20satellites%20launched%20by%20the%20Starlink%20program%20as%20an%20example%2C%20they%20are%20numerous%2C%20densely%20packed%20and%20small%20in%20size%2C%20making%20the%20satellite%20network%20extremely%20resilient%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20noted.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20satellites%20are%20destroyed%2C%20there%20are%20redundancies%20to%20replace%20them.%20Therefore%2C%20using%20missiles%20to%20attack%20such%20satellites%20is%20highly%20inefficient.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESatellite%20swarms%20are%20becoming%20a%20crucial%20part%20of%20warfare.%20They%20have%20enabled%20Ukraine%2C%20for%20example%2C%20to%20provide%20connectivity%20for%20its%20forces%20when%20existing%20Internet%20and%20satellite%20communications%20facilities%20were%20destroyed.%20Thus%2C%20there's%20a%20need%20for%20destroying%20or%20disabling%20many%20small%20satellites%20in%20low-Earth%20orbit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChinese%20researchers%20envision%20the%20solution%20as%20flotillas%20of%20mass-produced%20laser%20subs%20that%20could%20be%20dispatched%20to%20oceans%20around%20the%20world.%20They%20would%20wait%20for%20tracking%20data%20from%20other%20non-submarine%20platforms%20to%20determine%20when%20a%20target%20satellite%20is%20overhead.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20satellite%20enters%20the%20attackable%20range%2C%20the%20laser%20weapon%20is%20raised.%20Due%20to%20the%20limitations%20of%20the%20submarine's%20detection%20equipment%2C%20other%20forces%20are%20required%20to%20provide%20satellite%20position%20guidance%20for%20the%20submarine%20to%20attack%20the%20satellite.%20After%20the%20attack%20is%20completed%2C%20the%20submarine%20can%20submerge%20and%20wait%20for%20the%20next%20mission%20or%20return%20to%20the%20home%20port.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%20to%20destroying%20satellites%2C%20these%20subs%20could%20also%20blast%20aircraft%20or%20land%20targets%20such%20as%20radars%20and%20oil%20refineries.%20The%20Chinese%20researchers%20estimated%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20modest%20150-kilowatt%20laser%20weapon%20on%20a%20submarine%20can%20damage%20the%20photoelectric%20detection%20equipment%20on%20an%20anti-submarine%20aircraft%20in%20one-fifth%20of%20a%20second%2C%20with%20an%20effective%20range%20of%20more%20than%2020%20kilometers%20%5B12%20miles%5D%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Post%20said.%20%26quot%3BContinuous%20firing%20could%20also%20penetrate%20the%20aircraft's%20fuselage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELaser%20subs%20could%20also%20shield%20China's%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-tests-new-sub-launched-ballistic-missile-reports-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eballistic%20missile%20submarines%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20detection.%20%26quot%3BThe%20escorting%20submarine%20can%20first%20use%20the%20laser%20weapon%20to%20interfere%20with%20or%20destroy%20overhead%20satellites%20in%20the%20sea%20area%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20the%20enemy's%20space-based%20surveillance%20system%20to%20function%2C%20thereby%20achieving%20the%20concealment%20of%20missile%20launches.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202019%2C%20the%20US%20Navy%20put%20out%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalinterest.org%2Fblog%2Freboot%2Flaser-submarines-paradi