s%20or%20are%20unlikely%20to%20have%20them%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2024%2F07%2F25%2Fthe-experiences-of-u-s-adults-who-dont-have-children%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20July%2025.%20The%20report%20is%20based%20on%20surveys%20Pew%20conducted%20between%20April%2029%20and%20May%2019%20with%202%2C542%20people%2050%20and%20older%20without%20kids%20and%20770%20people%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2018%20and%2049%20without%20kids%20and%20who%20say%20they%20are%20unlikely%20to%20have%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESnyder%20is%20an%20example%20of%20an%20American%20who%20just%20didn't%20want%20to%20have%20children.%20That%20decision%20has%20afforded%20her%20financial%20freedom%20%E2%80%94%20she%20said%20she%20has%20enough%20savings%20to%20support%20herself%20in%20retirement%20until%20she's%20110.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20she's%20avoided%20being%20sandwiched%20between%20caring%20for%20children%20and%20her%20parents.%20Snyder%20spent%20six%20years%20helping%20her%20mother%2C%20father%2C%20and%20stepmom%20transition%20into%20nursing%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20have%20children%20to%20worry%20about%20and%20pay%20for%20while%20I%20was%20caring%20for%20my%20parents%20in%20the%20nursing%20home%2C%20so%20I%20was%20just%20taking%20care%20of%20the%20older%20generation%20ahead%20of%20me%2C%20not%20sandwiched%20by%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20younger%20generation%2C%26quot%3B%20Snyder%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20earlier%20life%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESnyder%20married%20her%20late%20husband%20Phil%20in%201986%2C%20and%20they%20bought%20a%20small%20ranch%20in%20Beaverton%2C%20Oregon%2C%20where%20she%20still%20lives.%20She%20said%20they%20enjoyed%20a%20%26quot%3Bwonderful%20marriage%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20freedom%20to%20spend%20their%20time%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESnyder%20said%20not%20having%20kids%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-dinks-winning-childfree-economy-finances-income-vacation-retirement-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallowed%20her%20and%20Phil%20to%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20extensively%20in%20the%20US%2C%20camping%20across%20the%20Western%20part%20of%20the%20country%20and%20frequenting%20ski%20destinations%20like%20Mount%20Hood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20environment%20%E2%80%94%20not%20money%20%E2%80%94%20was%20the%20reason%20she%20didn't%20have%20children%2C%20Snyder%20said%20it%20allowed%20her%20and%20Phil%20more%20breathing%20room%20in%20their%20financial%20and%20social%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20we%20had%20more%20disposable%20money%20gave%20us%20the%20freedom%20to%20do%20more%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20she%20and%20Phil%20were%20able%20to%20go%20out%20to%20dinner%20without%20concerns%20about%20finding%20and%20paying%20for%20childcare.%20Furthermore%2C%20they%20could%20spend%20money%20on%20things%20like%20season%20box%20seats%20at%20the%20Oregon%20Ballet%20Theater%20that%20they%20probably%20would%20have%20passed%20on%20if%20they%20had%20kids%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2658ae4-9578-4d3e-a456-2a987c2603b6%5C%22%3EThe%20benefits%20of%20a%20child-free%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOhio%2C%20Snyder%20said%20she%20felt%20some%20social%20pressure%20from%20her%20family%20and%20friends%20to%20have%20children%2C%20though%20she%20was%20steadfast%20in%20her%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Iowa%2C%20Snyder%20moved%20to%20Oregon%2C%20where%20she%20began%20working%20in%20communications.%20Snyder%20worked%20for%20the%20Oregon%20Department%20of%20Transportation%2C%20Portland%20Public%20Schools%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20Oregon%20Department%20of%20Human%20Services%2C%20and%20other%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESnyder%20saw%20the%20biggest%20benefit%20of%20not%20having%20kids%20as%20the%20time%20it%20allowed%20her%20and%20her%20husband%20to%20travel%20and%20indulge%20in%20hobbies%20together%2C%20like%20hiking%20and%20attending%20lectures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESnyder%20said%20she's%20grateful%20for%20her%20financial%20freedom.%20She%20said%20she's%20seen%20many%20of%20her%20friends%20stuck%20in%20situations%20where%20they're%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehelping%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20children's%20finances%2C%20such%20as%20education%20or%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCollege%20costs%20more%2C%20houses%20cost%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Snyder%20said.%20%26quot%3BParents%20are%20picking%20up%20the%20difference%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20to%20be%2C%20among%20people%20I%20know%2C%20an%20ongoing%20issue.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESnyder%20said%20as%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibecession-recession-hiring-outlook-american-economic-sentiment-rising-prices-recovery-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeel%20the%20economy%20is%20more%20unaffordable%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20parents%20are%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20helping%20their%20children%20in%20ways%20they%20might%20not%20have%20anticipated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESnyder%20said%20she%20respects%20people%20who%20have%20children%20and%20says%20those%20who%20choose%20to%20do%20so%20must%20make%20intentional%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20power%20to%20parents%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20should%20be%20spending%20their%20time%20and%20their%20money%20on%20their%20kids.%20That's%20the%20whole%20point%20of%20raising%20a%20good%20kid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20there%20are%20many%20people%20who'd%20like%20to%20have%20children%20but%20can't%20afford%20it.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20previously%20reported%20on%20DINKs%3Cstrong%3E%20%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhich%20stands%20for%20dual%20income%2C%20no%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20who%20can't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22h