iness%20as%20his%20family's%20sole%20source%20of%20income%20and%20cashed%20out%20his%20retirement%20fund%20to%20finance%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHocker%20is%20running%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsweaty-startups-millennial-business-owners-entrepreneurship-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esweaty%20startup%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20term%20coined%20by%20the%20entrepreneur%20Nick%20Huber%2C%20who%20owns%20nine%20such%20companies%20and%20has%20amassed%20communities%20on%20X%20and%20Reddit.%20Sweaty%20startups%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-collar-job-demand-growth-white-collar-layoffs-ai-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblue-collar%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20often%20in%20unglamorous%20or%20laborious%20fields%20like%20septic%20services%2C%20car%20washes%2C%20or%20lawn%20care.%20It's%20what%20your%20grandparents%20would've%20just%20called%20a%20small%20business%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20tongue-in-cheek%20answer%20to%20the%20Silicon%20Valley-style%20entrepreneurship%20being%20glorified%20in%20culture%20at%20that%20time.%20The%20community%20boasts%20success%20stories%20of%20profitable%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F22-year-old-bought-car-wash-passive-income-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecar%20wash%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20successful%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fadvisor%2Fbusiness%2Fstart-a-vending-machine-business%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evending%20machine%3C%2Fa%3E%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20who%20is%20truly%20wealthy%20in%20these%20small%20towns%2C%20people%20who%20are%20eating%20at%20the%20nice%20restaurants%20and%20at%20the%20nice%20country%20clubs%2C%20you'll%20find%20that%20they%20didn't%20have%20new%20ideas%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Huber%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThey%20didn't%20have%20tech%20startups%20aimed%20at%20changing%20the%20world%2C%20and%20they%20didn't%20build%20a%20billion-dollar%20business.%20Most%20of%20them%20did%20something%20common%20or%20boring%2C%20and%20they%20just%20did%20it%20uncommonly%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20sweaty%20startup%20owners%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20loved%20the%20work%20and%20felt%20fulfilled%2C%20many%20said%20it%20was%20becoming%20harder%20to%20scale%20up.%20Though%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fcesan.nr0.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsumer%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20on%20the%20rise%20since%202020%2C%20with%20a%20marked%20shift%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhate-spending-consumers-economic-sentiment-retail-sales-inflation-gdp-growth-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrom%20goods%20to%20services%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20business%20owners%20generally%20blamed%20customers'%20tightening%20budgets.%20The%20reasons%20likely%20also%20include%20high%20interest%20rates%20and%20increased%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f0d4786b-e1d6-4b04-aa79-57bb464d6dd3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrowth%20is%20challenging%2C%20but%20sweaty%20startups%20still%20provide%20plenty%20of%20opportunities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHuber%20said%20he%20saw%20sweaty%20startups%20become%20more%20popular%20in%20the%20first%20two%20years%20of%20the%20pandemic%20following%20mass%20layoffs%20and%20a%20rethinking%20of%20work.%20While%20some%20entrepreneurs%20go%20into%20these%20businesses%20hoping%20to%20strike%20it%20rich%20%E2%80%94%20some%20have%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Fsweatystartup%2Fcomments%2F15mcknl%2Fhow_to_handle_the_stigma_of_leaving_a_white%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleft%20Wall%20Street%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20do%20so%20%E2%80%94%20many%20do%20so%20because%20they%20want%20more%20flexibility%20and%20time%20with%20family%2C%20financial%20risks%20be%20damned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuber%20said%20that%20in%20some%20ways%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillionaire-small-business-entrepreneur-revenue-census-construction-finance-real-estate-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebusiness%20landscape%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20getting%20harder%20for%20founders%20to%20break%20into.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-reserve-interest-rates-jerome-powell-borrowing-costs-stock-market-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHigh%20interest%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20hurt%20owners%20borrowing%20cash%20to%20open%20their%20businesses.%20While%20the%20number%20of%20sweaty%20startup%20founders%20seeking%20venture%20capital%20is%20likely%20low%2C%20Huber%20said%20he's%20known%20it%20to%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20venture-backed%20businesses%20are%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20trouble%20and%20hurting%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Huber%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20raised%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20in%202021%20and%202022%2C%20and%20now%20they're%20seeing%20the%20economic%20headwinds%20from%20inflation%20and%20are%20unable%20to%20raise%20their%20next%20round.%20They're%20kind%20of%20stuck.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-firms-start-recruiting-early-investment-bank-apollo-kkr-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprivate%20equity%3C%2Fa%3E%20firms%20have%20been%20eyeing%20smaller%20businesses%20in%20these%20industries%2C%20which%20could%20tighten%20competition.%20For%20instance%2C%20private%20equity%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexecutive-coaching-benefits-according-to-graham-weaver-ceo-alpine-investors-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlpine%20Investors%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20partnered%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Falpineinvestors.com%2Fportfolio%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20industries%20such%20as%20HVAC%2C%20plumbing%20and%20electrical%2C%20roofing%20repair%2C%20and%20tree%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Investment%20Council%2C%20a%20lobbying%20and%20research%20organization%20for%20the%20private-equity%20industry%2C%20estimates%20that%20private%20equity%20owns%20only%20about%202.5%25%20of%20all%20middle-market%20businesses%2C%20or%20those%20earning%20about%20%2410%20million%20to%20%241%20billion%2C%20in%20the%20US.%20Still%2C%20some%20small%20businesses%20look%20to%20private%20equity%20to%20scale%20their%20businesses%20in%20different%20markets%2C%20even%20if%20that%20means%20overhauling%20operations%20in%20some%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSmall%20businesses%20partner%20with%20private-equity%20firms%20because%20they%20provide%20access%20to%20capital%20and%20organizational%20support%20to%20help%20companies%20grow%2C%26quot%3B%20Drew%20Maloney%2C%20the%20council's%20president%20and%20CEO%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20business%20owners%20who%20left%20the%20corporate%20world%20to%20run%20a%20sweaty%20startup%20said%20it%20came%20with%20plenty%20of%20benefits%20but%20lots%20of%20stress%20about%20staying%20afloat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStan%20Chen%2C%2036%2C%20worked%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblackrock-news-updates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlackRock%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20in%20mortgage%20sales%2C%20and%20then%20at%20a%20global%20payments%20company%20before%20getting%20into%20a%20sweaty%20startup.%20His%20family%20operated%20restaurants%20in%20Boston%20for%20decades%2C%20and%20after%20years%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20he%20wanted%20to%20transition%20to%20a%20service-type%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20%26quot%3Bdidn't%20want%20to%20have%20a%20boss%2C%20climb%20the%20corporate%20ladder%2C%20and%20deal%20with%20office%20politics.%26quot%3B%20Referring%20to%20his%20family%2C%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20immigrants%20who%20barely%20speak%20English%20that%20came%20here%20with%20%2420%20can%20run%20a%20business%20of%20three%20to%20four%20restaurants%20and%20basically%20become%20millionaires%20and%20have%20a%20nice%20middle-class%20lifestyle%2C%20I'm%20pretty%20sure%20I%20can%20do%20it%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stan%20Chen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66acdf13a5247369a3e90331%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStan%20Chen%20owns%20BerryClean%20in%20San%20Francisco.%3Cp%3EStan%20Chen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20saw%20that%20BerryClean%2C%20a%20house-cleaning%20service%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20was%20for%20sale.%20After%20meeting%20with%20the%20management%20and%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20who%20he%20said%20reminded%20him%20of%20his%20family%20%E2%80%94%20he%20acquired%20the%20company%20in%20July%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20when%20the%20pandemic%20hit%20he%20lost%2090%25%20of%20his%20business%2C%20but%20he%20applied%20for%20loans%20and%20improvised.%20The%20company%20built%20its%20own%20%26quot%3Bmini%20Uber%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20Chen%20said%2C%20offering%20rides%20in%20its%2020%20cars%20and%20minivans.%20When%20demand%20for%20cleaning%20picked%20up%20again%2C%20he%20sometimes%20worked%2018-hour%20days%20to%20keep%20operations%20running.%20The%20company's%20washers%20and%20vacuums%20would%20regularly%20break%20down%2C%20and%20he%20would%20sometimes%20have%20to%20do%20laundry%20at%20his%20home%20to%20keep%20clients%20satisfied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOperations%20have%20grown%20recently%2C%20and%20he%20said%20he's%20seen%20staff%20get%20their%20lives%20better%20on%20track%20and%20%26quot%3Bachieve%20the%20American%20dream.%26quot%3B%20Despite%20the%20company's%20growth%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20though%2C%20Chen%20said%20business%20had%20gotten%20tougher%20recently%20with%20growing%20competition%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20He%20said%20he%20had%20to%20raise%20prices%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20inflation.%20He%20noticed%20that%20people%20wanted%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-cleaning-business-side-hustle-low-startup-costs-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecleaning%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20his%20area%2C%20and%20the%20company%20dug%20into%20profits%20to%20increase%20its%20advertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20get%20into%20this%20kind%20of%20business%20for%20the%20wrong%20reasons%2C%20because%20they%20listen%20to%20a%20podcast%20or%20they're%20on%20social%20media%2C%20thinking%20it's%20easy%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Chen%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20easy%20money%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20hardest%20money%20there%20is.%20You%20have%20to%20earn%20your%20keep%20every%20day%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20get%20your%20hands%20dirty.%20If%20you%20don't%20do%20a%20good%20job%2C%20you're%20fired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlejandro%20Florez%2C%2027%2C%20the%20president%20of%20The%20Cleaning%20Pros%20of%20America%20in%20Bradenton%2C%20Florida%2C%20said%20the%20growing%20investments%20in%20janitorial%20companies%20in%20his%20area%20were%20in%20some%20ways%20antithetical%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20sweaty%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20small%20cleaning%20businesses%20are%20pulled%20up%20by%20the%20bootstraps%2C%20and%20we%20usually%20start%20them%20out%20of%20necessity%20as%20our%20only%20avenue%20of%20making%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Florez%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221089%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alejandro%20Florez%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66acdf8d393cd3c8629ad64f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22817%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlejandro%20Florez%20runs%20Cleaning%20Pros%20of%20America.%3Cp%3EAlejandro%20Florez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20of%20his%20parents%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffrank-baez-earns-nyu-nursing-degree-used-to-be-janitor-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejanitors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20when%20he%20was%20a%20senior%20in%20high%20school%20he%20started%20a%20small%20cleaning%20company%20that%20he%20grew%20by%20knocking%20on%20doors%20and%20cold-calling.%20He%20relied%20on%20trial%20and%20error%20and%20supplier%20advice%20for%20pricing%2C%20production%20rates%2C%20and%20cleaning%20strategies%20for%20different%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20year%20he's%20had%20nearly%20%242%20million%20in%20revenue%20with%20two%20dozen%20employees%20and%20over%2030%20clients.%20He%20hopes%20to%20grow%20over%20the%20next%20decade%20by%20expanding%20to%20Jacksonville%20or%20Orlando.%20Still%2C%20he%20said%20that%20because%20the%20pandemic%20helped%20the%20cleaning%20industry%20%26quot%3Bmassively%2C%26quot%3B%20markets%20became%20much%20more%20saturated.%20He%20estimated%20that%2045%25%20to%2055%25%20of%20his%20overhead%20went%20to%20paying%20his%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20our%20market%2C%20even%20though%20it's%20very%20profitable%20and%20attractive%2C%20there's%20a%20low%20barrier%20to%20entry%2C%26quot%3B%20Florez%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20more%20people%20at%20the%20table%20wanting%20to%20eat%20from%20that%20table.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlorez%20said%20the%20growth%20of%20private-equity%20investment%20in%20his%20area%20had%20made%20competition%20even%20more%20difficult.%20Since%202021%2C%20he%20said%2C%20he's%20been%20approached%20by%20a%20dozen%20private-equity%20firms%20wanting%20to%20invest%20in%20his%20company%2C%20but%20he's%20turned%20them%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20get%20private%20equity%20into%20the%20mix%2C%20they're%20bringing%20a%20different%20dimension%20of%20business%20and%20being%20able%20to%20scale%20it%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20Florez%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20firms%20that%20can%20operate%20on%2010%25%20net%20profit%2C%20which%20I%20can't%20do.%20There%20are%20firms%20out%20there%20that%20are%20being%20a%20lot%20more%20aggressive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b453f9d2-5f80-484d-b4ca-0b542234b938%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrial%20and%20error%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20works%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20sweaty-startup%20owners%2C%20staying%20ahead%20of%20the%20competition%20requires%20bouncing%20from%20company%20to%20company%20based%20on%20changing%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Salisbury%2C%2035%2C%20has%20been%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-side-hustles-for-introverts-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eentrepreneur%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20he%20was%2016.%20He%20started%20a%20small%20house-painting%20business%20while%20in%20high%20school%20and%20a%20few%20other%20companies%20in%20his%2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chris%20Salisbury%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66acdeb6a5247369a3e90314%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChris%20Salisbury%20runs%20nuDoors%2C%20which%20specializes%20in%20replacement%20cabinet%20doors.%3Cp%3EChris%20Salisbury%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20he%20sold%20everything%20he%20owned%3B%20moved%20to%20Brooklyn%2C%20New%20York%3B%20and%20decided%20to%20start%20a%20new%20business%20while%20living%20in%20a%20wood%20shop.%20With%20two%20friends%2C%20he%20launched%20Spayce%2C%20a%20commercial%20cleaning%20and%20handyman%20company%20that%20worked%20with%20high-profile%20clients%20like%20BuzzFeed%20%E2%80%94%20Salisbury%20said%20the%20business%20brought%20in%20%24120%2C000%20in%20its%20first%20week%20and%20over%20%244%20million%20in%20its%20first%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Spayce%20manufactured%20Covid%20barriers%20and%20secured%20new%20contracts%20with%20clients.%20Salisbury%20also%20launched%20the%20brand%20We%20Paint%20Kitchen%20