orce%2C%20so%20they%20manage%20to%20push%20through%20these%20defensive%20lines%20and%20then%20reach%20the%20operative%20space%26quot%3B%20of%20Crimea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20and%20when%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20do%20reach%20Crimea%2C%20Sumlenny%20said%2C%20they%20will%20be%20able%20to%20destroy%20the%20Kerch%20Bridge%20and%20the%20last%20ferry%20road%20over%20the%20Sea%20of%20Azov%2C%20cutting%20off%20all%20of%20Russia's%20supply%20lines%20to%20the%20peninsula%20and%20isolating%20Russian%20forces.%20Using%20long-range%20missiles%20to%20cut-off%20supply%20lines%20was%20a%20crucial%20element%20of%20Ukraine's%20grinding%20and%20successful%20liberation%20of%20the%20city%20of%20Kherson%20in%20late%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESumlenny%20added%20that%20Crimea%20has%20historically%20been%20vulnerable%20to%20offensives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20case%20in%20history%20when%20anyone%20could%20defend%20Crimea%20from%20an%20attack%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201921%2C%20the%20Soviet%20Union's%20Red%20Army%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcourses.lumenlearning.com%2Fsuny-hccc-worldhistory2%2Fchapter%2Fthe-russian-civil-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrushed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20White%20Russians%20and%20took%20control%20of%20the%20peninsula%2C%20and%20in%201941%2C%20the%20Axis%20powers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iwm.org.uk%2Fhistory%2Foperation-barbarossa-and-germanys-failure-in-the-soviet-union%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvaded%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20during%20Operation%20Barbarossa%2C%20with%20their%20land%20forces%20laying%20siege%20to%20Sevastopol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Red%20Army%20launched%20a%20massive%20counter-attack%20in%20late%201943%20with%202.6%20million%20men%20that%20pushed%20the%20Germans%20back%20and%20weakened%20their%20hold%20on%20Crimea.%20After%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20of%20German%20occupation%2C%20a%20Soviet%20force%20of%20over%20450%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fplace%2FCrimea%2FHistory%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregained%3C%2Fa%3E%20control%20of%20Crimea%20in%201944.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wilsoncenter.org%2Fpublication%2Fwhy-did-russia-give-away-crimea-sixty-years-ago%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransferred%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Soviet%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20republics%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20%E2%80%94%20in%201954%2C%20until%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20Ukrainian%20independence%20in%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%202014%2C%20Russian%20forces%20invaded%20and%20occupied%20the%20peninsula%20before%20annexing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20all%20the%20cases%20when%20armies%20were%20clearly%20ready%20to%20fight%20and%20defend%20their%20positions%2C%20we%20can%20say%20that%20Crimea%20is%20practically%20an%20undefendable%20fortress%2C%26quot%3B%20Sumlenny%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20from%20my%20perspective%2C%20the%20moment%20the%20Ukrainian%20army%20will%20appear%20on%20the%20land%20bridge%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Isthmus%20of%20Pereko%20%E2%80%94%20between%20Crimea%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20Russians%20will%20face%20a%20very%20simple%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Beither%20they%20retreat%20immediately%20from%20Crimea%20or%20get%20slaughtered%20or%20captured.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20experts%2C%20however%2C%20struck%20a%20more%20cautious%20tone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETemnycky%20said%20a%20full-scale%20invasion%20to%20try%20to%20retake%20Crimea%20is%20%26quot%3Bvery%20unlikely%26quot%3B%20due%20to%20the%20huge%20Ukrainian%20losses%20that%20would%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriedman%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20said%20such%20an%20operation%20would%20require%20a%20%26quot%3Bcataclysmic%20Russian%20collapse%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20said%20is%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20unlikely%20though%20not%20impossible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20there%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-general-warns-russia-nuclear-weapon-stalemate-ukraine-war-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efears%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Russia%20would%20consider%20nuclear%20force%20if%20its%20troops%20were%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20losing%20Crimea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECancian%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20of%20its%20difficulty%2C%20retaking%20Crimea%20would%20be%20the%20last%20event%20of%20the%20war%2C%20not%20an%20intermediate%20event.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-pushed-russian-fleet-out-of-crimea-but-faces-tough-battle-to-retake-it-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722672002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a22dffaab37011780a52d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-pushed-russian-fleet-out-of-crimea-but-faces-tough-battle-to-retake-it-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ukraine%20has%20forced%20Russia's%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20out%20of%20Crimea%2C%20but%20it%20faces%20an%20uphill%20battle%20to%20retake%20the%20peninsula%2C%20experts%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirlet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-pushed-russian-fleet-out-of-crimea-but-faces-tough-battle-to-retake-it-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Iran%20Begins%20The%20Purge%20After%20Hamas%20Chief's%20Assassination%20In%20Tehran%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20killing%20of%20Hamas%20leader%20Ismail%20Haniyeh%20in%20its%20capital%20Tehran%2C%20Iran%20has%20arrested%20over%20two%20dozen%20individuals%2C%20including%20high-ranking%20intelligence%20officers%2C%20military%20officials%2C%20and%20staff%20at%20a%20military-run%20guesthouse%20in%20the%20capital%2C%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F08%2F03%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Firan-security-response-hamas-assassination.html%3Fsmid%3Dnytcore-android-share%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20elite%20intelligence%20agency%20Mossad%20enlisted%20Iranian%20security%20agents%20to%20plant%20explosives%20at%20the%20guesthouse%20where%20Haniyeh%20was%20staying.%20Haniyeh%2C%20who%20headed%20Hamas's%20political%20office%20in%20Qatar%2C%20was%20in%20Tehran%20for%20the%20inauguration%20of%20Iran's%20new%20president.%20The%20assassination%2C%20occurring%20just%20hours%20after%20the%20president's%20swearing-in%20ceremony%2C%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20massive%20intelligence%20and%20security%20failure%20for%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20perception%20that%20Iran%20can%20neither%20protect%20its%20homeland%20nor%20its%20key%20allies%20could%20be%20fatal%20for%20the%20Iranian%20regime%20because%20it%20basically%20signals%20to%20its%20foes%20that%20if%20they%20can't%20topple%20the%20Islamic%20Republic%2C%20they%20can%20decapitate%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ali%20Vaez%2C%20Iran%20director%20for%20the%20International%20Crisis%20Group%2C%20told%20New%20York%20Times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-hired-iranian-agents-to-assassinate-hamas-chief-in-tehran-report-6252736%5C%22%3E2%20Iran%20Agents%2C%20Bombs%20In%203%20Rooms%3A%20Inside%20Mossad's%20Kill%20Op%20For%20Hamas%20Chief%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIranian%20security%20forces%20conducted%20thorough%20searches%20of%20the%20guesthouse%20compound.%20They%20detained%20staff%2C%20confiscated%20electronic%20devices%2C%20and%20scrutinised%20surveillance%20footage%20and%20guest%20lists.%20Senior%20military%20and%20intelligence%20officials%20responsible%20for%20Tehran's%20security%20were%20also%20interrogated%2C%20with%20several%20placed%20under%20arrest%20pending%20further%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20compound%2C%20managed%20by%20the%20IRGC%2C%20housed%20Haniyeh%20in%20a%20room%20he%20frequently%20used%20during%20his%20Tehran%20visits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran's%20Islamic%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20Corps%20or%20IRGC's%20specialised%20intelligence%20unit%20for%20espionage%20has%20taken%20the%20lead%20in%20the%20investigation.%20The%20unit%20is%20actively%20pursuing%20suspects%20to%20uncover%20the%20network%20responsible%20for%20the%20assassination.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIranian%20and%20Hamas%20officials%20have%20accused%20Israel%20of%20orchestrating%20the%20assassination%2C%20a%20stance%20supported%20by%20several%20US.%20officials.%20Israel%2C%20maintaining%20its%20stance%20on%20eliminating%20Hamas's%20military%20capabilities%2C%20has%20not%20acknowledged%20responsibility%20for%20the%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20The%20Telegraph%2C%20Israel's%20initial%20plan%20was%20to%20assassinate%20Haniyeh%20in%20May%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20Tehran%20for%20the%20funeral%20of%20former%20Iranian%20President%20Ebrahim%20Raisi.%20The%20operation%20was%20aborted%20due%20to%20overwhelming%20crowds%2C%20which%20posed%20a%20major%20risk%20of%20failure%2C%20according%20to%20two%20Iranian%20officials%20who%20spoke%20to%20The%20Telegraph.%20Two%20agents%2C%20working%20under%20Mossad's%20direction%2C%20placed%20explosive%20devices%20in%20three%20separate%20rooms%20of%20the%20IRGC%20guesthouse%20in%20northern%20Tehran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20assassination%20has%20been%20confirmed%20by%20officials%20within%20the%20IRGC%2C%20who%20now%20believe%20Mossad%20employed%20agents%20from%20the%20Ansar-al-Mahdi%20protection%20unit%2C%20a%20group%20responsible%20for%20safeguarding%20high-ranking%20officials%20inside%20and%20outside%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0Israel%20has%20previously%20targeted%20Iranian%20nuclear%20scientists%20and%20military%20commanders%2C%20including%20the%20high-profile%20killing%20of%20Mohsen%20Fakhrizadeh%20in%202020.%20These%20operations%20have%20often%20involved%20sophisticated%20technology%20and%20precise%20execution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDays%20before%20Haniyeh's%20assassination%2C%20Iran's%20Minister%20of%20Intelligence%2C%20Seyed%20Esmaeil%20Khatib%2C%20claimed%20success%20in%20dismantling%20a%20Mossad%20infiltrator%20network.%20However%2C%20Haniyeh's%20killing%20contradicted%20these%20assurances%20of%20any%20security%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722672000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Ffbo3qqd_ismail-haniyeh-_625x300_03_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fismail-haniyeh-mossad-iran-iran-begins-the-purge-after-hamas-chiefs-assassination-in-tehran-6253885%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20response%20to%20the%20killing%20of%20Hamas%20leader%20Ismail%20Haniyeh%20in%20its%20capital%20Tehran%2C%20Iran%20has%20arrested%20over%20two%20dozen%20individuals%2C%20including%20high-ranking%20intelligence%20officers%2C%20military%20officials%2C%20and%20staff%20at%20a%20military-run%20guesthouse%20in%20the%20capital.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fismail-haniyeh-mossad-iran-iran-begins-the-purge-after-hamas-chiefs-assassination-in-tehran-6253885%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fismail-haniyeh-mossad-iran-iran-begins-the-purge-after-hamas-chiefs-assassination-in-tehran-6253885%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fismail-haniyeh-mossad-iran-iran-begins-the-purge-after-hamas-chiefs-assassination-in-tehran-6253885%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Taapsee%20on%20not%20wanting%20to%20be%20highest-paid%20actress%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722671995000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic